ontent_hash":"ace67045c469c4e490bf4aec6ad88c18d50afa9829ca2e2cca3e836b461c5eb1","event_uuid":"6e911229-fe6d-4a5e-b36d-4d07189552ac","position":{"commit_sha":"051c4d123cce3970731e610f5a0d915ce5b9baf2","position":"1784838352105689001-6e911229-fe6d-4a5e-b36d-4d07189552ac"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"3e50bad85d61b6800926fc21c397248bfd0475745bb86863a7e84c830f5d3758","event_uuid":"c63ad81e-f153-4923-81ae-a702ffea9eea","position":{"commit_sha":"051c4d123cce3970731e610f5a0d915ce5b9baf2","position":"1784838352416963001-c63ad81e-f153-4923-81ae-a702ffea9eea"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"}],"bridge_alerts":[],"claim_harness":null,"claim_remote_session":null,"claimed_session":null,"comments":[],"created_at":1784517464697193001,"creation_channel":"cli","deps":[{"link_uuid":"5da4ec76-0984-46f6-a62b-6b25c0a31eee","relation":"depends_on","target_id":"9597-1b85-d2ab-4eed"},{"link_uuid":"2c16baad-289b-4023-afcf-058f2efd61e9","relation":"depends_on","target_id":"e7a0-acef-ec67-42bb"},{"link_uuid":"6bd63dc2-3d8c-4f9b-8de0-b0a6b133c549","relation":"depends_on","target_id":"3b30-2168-ba16-41fc"}],"description":"## Problem\nThe scc LOC/size analyzer for the code_health lens: produces the `loc` payload of `AnalyzerResult [rebar:3b30-2168-ba16-41fc]` from `scc --format json`, fails closed (Unavailable) when scc is unavailable, and never fabricates zeros.\n\n## Approach & rationale (G6/T1/A1 — self-contained, no cross-layer coupling)\n`scc_loc.py` is SELF-CONTAINED: it invokes scc via its own `subprocess` and parses the JSON itself (a trivial, stable read of per-file `Code`+`Location`). It does NOT import from `rebar.grounding` — the `analyzers` package stays independent of the grounding layer (clean layering; avoids a metrics<->grounding dependency). Rationale (A1 ANTI-FP): the scc JSON extraction is ~10 lines of field access, NOT a shared abstraction worth cross-layer coupling; grounding's own `_scc_files` serves a different consumer (Engine-B detectors). If a third consumer ever appears (Rule-of-Three), extraction to a shared module is deferred to then (YAGNI now). New analyzers live in `analyzers/` (NOT the quarantined `adapters/`).\n\n## Concrete contracts (single source of truth — 0734 reads these)\n- ENTRY POINT: `scc_loc.analyze(repo_root, scan_roots=None, *, run=_run_scc) -> AnalyzerResult | Unavailable`. `run` is an injectable runner (default shells `[\"scc\",\"--format\",\"json\", <root>]` via `subprocess.run`) so tests need no live scc.\n- LOC PAYLOAD: `AnalyzerResult.loc = {\"files\": {<relpath:str>: <loc:int>}, \"max_loc\": <int>}`. scc JSON is TWO-LEVEL: `data` is a list of language-group objects, each with a `\"Files\"` array of per-file entries `{\"Code\": int, \"Location\": str}`. The parser flattens BOTH levels (`for group in data: for entry in group.get(\"Files\", []): ...`) — the same flattening grounding's `_scc_files` does; iterating `data` directly would yield nothing. Each `Location` is made repo-relative and POSIX-normalized before use as a key: `files[PurePath(os.path.relpath(entry[\"Location\"], repo_root)).as_posix()] = entry[\"Code\"]`. `max_loc = max(files.values(), default=0)`.\n- `_ACCRUING_SINCE = \"2026-01-01T00:00:00+00:00\"` — the SAME module-level ISO-8601 constant value used by the existing metrics reader modules (git_metrics.py / event_metrics.py both define `_ACCRUING_SINCE = \"2026-01-01T00:00:00+00:00\"`).\n- FAIL-CLOSED (returns `Unavailable(reason, _ACCRUING_SINCE)` AND emits `logger.warning(\"scc unavailable: %s\", reason)`): scc binary missing (`FileNotFoundError` from `subprocess`), non-zero exit, empty stdout, or unparseable JSON. A SUCCESSFUL empty result (`[]`, e.g. all-ignored tree) is NOT unavailable -> `AnalyzerResult(loc={\"files\": {}, \"max_loc\": 0})`.\n\n## Grounding (E4 — verified via Read)\n- CONFIRMED scc emits per-file LOC as JSON (`scc --format json`); each file entry has `Code`/`Location` (engine_b_backends.py:376,412 read exactly these, independently).\n- `AnalyzerResult` / `Unavailable(reason, accruing_since)` from prerequisite `[rebar:3b30-2168-ba16-41fc]`; `[metrics]` extra `[rebar:9597-1b85-d2ab-4eed]`; `[code_health]` config `[rebar:e7a0-acef-ec67-42bb]` (all depends_on edges recorded). This adapter does NOT use `resolve_analyzer` (it IS an analyzer implementation).\n\n## Acceptance criteria (observable + proving command; tests use the injectable `run`, no live scc)\n- [ ] parse: `run` returns canned scc JSON for files at 100 & 850 LOC -> `analyze` returns `AnalyzerResult` with `loc[\"files\"]` keyed by repo-relative POSIX paths and `loc[\"max_loc\"] == 850`. PROVE: `pytest -q tests/unit/metrics/test_scc_loc.py::test_parse`.\n- [ ] missing binary: `run` raises `FileNotFoundError` -> `Unavailable(reason, _ACCRUING_SINCE)`, no crash, no zeros. PROVE: `pytest -q tests/unit/metrics/test_scc_loc.py::test_missing_binary`.\n- [ ] non-zero exit AND unparseable/empty stdout each -> `Unavailable`. PROVE: `pytest -q tests/unit/metrics/test_scc_loc.py::test_bad_output`.\n- [ ] successful empty output (`[]`) -> `AnalyzerResult(loc={\"files\":{},\"max_loc\":0})`, not Unavailable. PROVE: `pytest -q tests/unit/metrics/test_scc_loc.py::test_empty_tree`.\n- [ ] (supplementary) live scc smoke, skipif scc absent. PROVE: `pytest -q tests/unit/metrics/test_scc_loc.py::test_live -m integration`.\n\n## Rollback: revert is a clean delete of the two new files (no existing file is modified).\n## Dependencies: 3b30, 9597, e7a0 (recorded depends_on).\n## Files likely touched\n- src/rebar/metrics/analyzers/__init__.py (new; package marker)\n- src/rebar/metrics/analyzers/scc_loc.py (new; self-contained scc invoke + parse -> AnalyzerResult.loc)\n- tests/unit/metrics/test_scc_loc.py (new)\n## Estimated scope: M","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[{"path":"src/rebar/metrics/analyzers/scc_loc.py","reason":"new LOC adapter"},{"path":"src/rebar/metrics/analyzers/_scc.py","reason":"new shared scc JSON parse extracted from grounding"},{"path":"src/rebar/grounding/engine_b_backends.py","reason":"point grounding backend at shared helper (single normalizer)"},{"path":"tests/unit/metrics/test_scc_loc.py","reason":"new: import-assertion proof of reuse + monkeypatched runner"}],"keyring":[],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[["depends_on","3b30-2168-ba16-41fc"],["depends_on","9597-1b85-d2ab-4eed"],["depends_on","e7a0-acef-ec67-42bb"],["parent","839b-f6d2-7e1a-4051"]],"parent_id":"839b-f6d2-7e1a-4051","parent_status_uuid":"6e911229-fe6d-4a5e-b36d-4d07189552ac","plan_review_phase":"execution","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":2,"reverts":[],"status":"in_progress","tags":["metrics","code-health"],"ticket_id":"18f9-5b75-b909-408c","ticket_type":"story","title":"LOC/size analyzer adapter via scc (deterministic shell-out, JSON parse)","verify_commands":[]},"source_event_uuids":["00fdf525-3243-44ae-91a4-9f949627bf45","5da4ec76-0984-46f6-a62b-6b25c0a31eee","2c16baad-289b-4023-afcf-058f2efd61e9","a1a0c65e-8737-43dc-9942-8b0c5604b9ed","94c87b8f-f5a0-4b7c-8a20-1f1d73c0f65e","464f277b-4cc5-4c47-849f-31ffeaa2aea8","6bd63dc2-3d8c-4f9b-8de0-b0a6b133c549","54e63ca6-3475-4edd-8120-5ba6a9f8cfb6","dfc915b8-f28c-4477-ab27-74ead355fbef","db9ed219-5e3d-4a34-b6de-47105c29a80e","005c2ac7-824b-4141-a924-03445030dccd","77c834a3-da63-4bbe-b3e5-8cde1036c731","4313cb9e-8db8-471e-b8e9-0d931e0951c7","d6cbb31b-ceb0-4945-88c0-8c